metadata.name: Night lights #11
metadata.description:
Don't fear the lights of the night,
the luminous path rises before you;
do not paralyze yourself or sink into serenity.

In your corner of the universe, prevent your eyelids from falling;
don't immerse yourself in the imagination of words, delve into your dreams.
And despite everything, don't consider abandonment or the passage of time.

Don't lose control.





Minted: December 2023

metadata.name: Music land #1
metadata.description:
Music
Music is not always sound!
Sometimes colors have harmony like musical notes
Sometimes lines like instruments add pleasure to life
Sometimes life without music is unbearable!
And without colors!

metadata.name: Self-Block #15
metadata.description:
When you block your own self, it won't matter if the whole universe opens itself wide before you. As long as you keep blocking yourself, you will only delay achieving what you are destined to.

I know where I want to be... I can almost see where I am going to be... only behind a set of impenetrable-looking walls. Walls built by none other than my own self. Trying really hard to pass through them, but it doesn't matter, as I always stop at the very last step.

Self-Block is a strong reminder for me to take that one last step and be forever free of my own blocks.

May you pass through your own self-blocks.

* * *

Press S to save as PNG. To save a larger image, open live view, add "&s=WIDTH_IN_PIXELS" to the end of the URL (e.g. "&s=1600"), press Enter and then press S.

metadata.name: Citta #197
metadata.description:
Citta as mind Citta as city. 

Citta is city of interconnected minds from future of Metropolis IX(Project id:13292), after singularity people uploaded their consciousness into inorganic self-constructing structures. 

There are 13 different mind-hives named with upper case letters, only "MC-00001" is monochrome rest is in color. "SCMB" and "SCCB' are in spiral formation due to their nature.

Press 1 to 8 export PNG 1000px to 8000px 
9 exports 10000px PNG 

Exports are dependent on CPU, so larger export might take time. Please be patient. If you cannot export reach me out.

Works best in Chrome browser. 

Created with p5.js and canvas api.
Murat Atimtay 2022 | @atimtay | www.muratatimtay.com

metadata.name: Generative Charts #01 Sushiswap Live Data #32
metadata.description:
Live data charts pulling blockchain data in real time through The Graph decentralized network from Sushiswap subgraph (https://thegraph.com/explorer/subgraph?id=0x4bb4c1b0745ef7b4642feeccd0740dec417ca0a0-0). 

Each chart is uniquely generated. There are 14 possible options of tokens that are visualized, 6 different options of variables (i.e. price USD, liquidity USD, etc..), 7 possible ranges of dates (how many days back), 5 different line types, and a very large number of possible colors. 

Once a chart is generated, it will keep showing live data for its configuration. This does not use a centralized API endpoint, but rather triggers a micro-transaction in GRT to pay for the query to get the latest data (forever covered as part of your mint cost).

⚠️ This generative token is HIGHLY experimental ⚠️ I will buy back any token at mint price for any reason no questions asked and that will always be an option. Put it for sale at mint price and message me on twitter @esclaponr and I will buy it back.

metadata.name: Code Page 437 // Ishihara #208
metadata.description:
In order to understand what you see before your eyes you must first open this artwork in both Firefox and any other web browser of your choice, at the same time, to experience it as intended.

A combination of ishihara palettes and cross-browser bugs are used to explore neurodiversity by forcing the viewer to take additional manual steps to see the world from a different perspective. A whole new understanding of colour blindness should unfold as you struggle through inaccessibility yourself.

The 640x400px canvas consists of 25 rows, with 80 columns per row for a total of 2000 letters, using only 16 glyphs from the Codepage 437 character set scaled to a resolution of 8x16 pixels per character.

Codepage 437 is the original IBM PC-ASCII font from August 1981, often referred to as the DOS font.

metadata.name: Multi-Biome #128
metadata.description:
Inspired by Jose Margulis's "Alpine Landscape"

Designed to be viewed as if you're walking past on the gallery wall, Multi-Biome is an interative play on perspective and scale. Each landscape is created from between 50 and 200 planes, slicing the landscape along a single axis.

Click and drag to rotate.

Press "s" in live view to save a png.

metadata.name: MOMENT #238
metadata.description:
An endless row of them making up each life. Some poignant, some inspiring, some grievous, some affirming - but most of them a tad boring, a bit generic, almost forgettable like bland fabric. How can a life constructed from such mundanity count for anything? Maybe thanks to the last one, the one that stitches them all together, like a punchline to an absurdist joke.

Generative art written in JavaScript + Canvas with a little bit of help from p5.js.

metadata.name: Triangle Subdivisions #443
metadata.description:
A study on geometric triangle subdivisions resulted in this artwork.
Only 638 bytes of JavaScript are needed to create a variety of different subdivisions (and no libraries are used). 

One tile will be generated for every byte of code.  

An article about this technique can be seen here:
https://josvromans.com/blog/2021/1/triangle-subdivisions/

metadata.name: pendula #103
metadata.description: A grid of 17x17 chaotic pendulums. Each pendulum consists of 17 layers, each following a different, randomly generated square shaped route. We draw different shapes and colors at the end of each pendulum, as all 17 layers do a full lap simultaneously.

metadata.name: Univercell #47
metadata.description:
⚗🦠🌌✨

The center of a digital, quantified space emits 2 560 000 particles through a sequence of expansions, contractions and perturbations. 🌌

Once formed, the evolution of the Univercell can be observed through a series of animations in the manner of a documentary. 🎥

Each Univercell is a unique random and deterministic composition. 🔮

(Click ‘open’ and go fullscreen for best experience !)

🎄🌟🪐🌈☀




-----
* Mint preview *

Minter will get a 1920x1920 PNG bitmap and an infinite animation.

-----
* Technics *

This experience is designed to be executed on a recent GPU (>2016) and displayed on 16/9 screens from FHD to 8K+ (1920x1080 → 7680x4320) at 60FPS for infinite duration.

The physics algorithms take around 20 seconds to generate one Univercell. During generation, a progress indication in percentage is displayed.

- JavaScript / ThreeJS / WebGL
- Unique generative and determinist animation (animation is seeded by the fxhash mint hash)
- Unlimited duration (no loop) / 6 documentary animations
- 20 seconds internal algorithm variations

-----
* Controls *

Keyboard "Space" : take a PNG capture of the current view frame (same ratio as window, max 1920x1080)

⚗ Empiric mode (empiric=on / see URL modifiers below)
Wheel/pinch : zoom in/out to observe the Univercell on different scales
Right click + drag : move the observation area
Keyboard "R" : enable automatic rotation of view

-----
* URL modifiers *

"&empiric=on"
Turn off animations and display a Univercell that can be manually explored.

"&demo=on"
Reduce the cinematics duration to 5 seconds. Allows faster cycling through documentary phases.

"&random=on"
Randomize documentary sequences order.


-----
@HAL09999 – December 21st, 2022
